# C-W to delete the whole word
Control-W: backward-kill-word

### Following tips taken from https://bluz71.github.io/2018/03/15/bash-shell-tweaks-tips.html

# cycle through completion choices
TAB: menu-complete
# shift tab for previous completion
"\e[Z": menu-complete-backward
# display all when first press tab
set show-all-if-ambiguous on
set colored-stats on
set colored-completion-prefix on
# set completion-ignore-case on
set completion-map-case on
set mark-symlinked-directories on
